#Linux command cheat sheet
Linux terminal is a user-friendly terminal 
To Execute a command by pressing the 'ENTER' key.

#Linux Directory Commands
•	pwd  - Display the location of the current working directory
•	mkdir <directory_name> -  Create a new directory under any directory.
•	rmdir <directory_name> - Delete a directory.
•	ls - Display a list of content of a directory.
•	cd - Change the current directory.

#Linux File commands:
•	touch <filename> - Create empty file
•	touch <fname1><fname2>...- Create multiple empty files
•	cat > <filename> //Enter file content - Create a file 
•	cat <file name> - Display the content of the file
•	rm <filename> - Remove a file
•	cp <existing filename> <new filename>copy a file or directory.
•	mv <filename> <new dirpath> move a file or a directory form one location to another location.
•	rename s’/oldname/newname/’ files- rename files
•	 rename ‘s/\.txt$/\.pdf/  *.txt/ rename txt files to pdf files


	





